ITEM NO.20               COURT NO.12               SECTION II-C
               S U P R E M E  C O U R T  O F  I N D I A
                       RECORD OF PROCEEDINGS
Petition(s) for Special Leave to Appeal (Crl.)  No(s).  9539/2025
[Arising out of impugned final judgment and order dated  27-05-2025
in MCRCA No. 773/2025 passed by the High Court of Chhatisgarh at 
Bilaspur]
RANJEET KUMAR GUPTA & ANR.                         Petitioner(s)
                                VERSUS
STATE OF CHHATTISGARH                              Respondent(s)
FOR ADMISSION 
IA No. 151617/2025 - EXEMPTION FROM FILING O.T.
 
Date : 07-07-2025 This matter was called on for hearing today.
CORAM :  HON'BLE MR. JUSTICE PANKAJ MITHAL
         HON'BLE MR. JUSTICE K.V. VISWANATHAN
[PARTIAL COURT WORKING DAYS BENCH]
For Petitioner(s)  Mr. Sameer Shrivastava, AOR
                   Mr. Niteen Kumar Sinha, Adv.
                   Mr. Vikram Pratap Singh, Adv.
                                
For Respondent(s)  
          UPON hearing the counsel the Court made the following
                             O R D E R
1. Issue notice, returnable within six weeks.
2. In the meantime, no coercive action shall be taken against the
petitioners, in pursuance to FIR No.126 of 2025, registered at
Police Station Amanaka, District Raipur, Chhattisgarh.
(VARSHA MENDIRATTA)                             (NIDHI MATHUR)
COURT MASTER (SH)                             COURT MASTER (NSH)
